messages.content: You are an AI assistant that helps people find information. You will receive a task and think step by step. Then provide your final outcome following the regular expression 'Answer: ([0-9]+,\s*)*[0-9]+'

Imagine a house with 21 rooms. Room 1 is connected to rooms 21, 5, 24, 9, 4, and 13. Room 2 is connected to rooms 22, 6, 10, 11, 7, and 14. Room 3 is connected to rooms 35, 41, 23, 12, 8, and 20. Room 4 is connected to rooms 13, 21, 5, 24, and 9. Room 5 is connected to rooms 24, 9, 13, and 21. Room 6 is connected to rooms 24, 10, 11, 7, and 14. Room 7 is connected to rooms 14, 22, 10, and 11. Room 8 is connected to rooms 20, 35, 41, 23, and 12. Room 9 is connected to rooms 13, 21, and 41. Room 10 is connected to rooms 11, 14, and 22. Room 11 is connected to rooms 14 and 22. Room 12 is connected to rooms 20, 35, 41, and 23. Room 13 is connected to rooms 21, and 24. Room 14 is connected to rooms 22. Room 20 is connected to rooms 35, 41, and 23. Room 21 is connected to room 24. Room 22 is connected to room 23. Room 23 is connected to rooms 35. Room 35 is connected to room 41. You have been told that there is a reward of 10 for visiting room 22. You are in room 24 and you have been told that there is no connection between room 24 and 6, but room 24 and 41 are now connected. From room 24, what is the path that yields the most reward? Please list the room numbers in order, separated by commas.

The first line contains an integer, T, denoting the number of test cases.
The first line of each test case contains two integers, N and M, denoting the number of rooms and the number of connections respectively.
The next line contains N space separated integers, A1, A2, ..., AN denoting the rooms.
The next line contains M space separated integers, B1, B2, ..., BM denoting the connections.

For each test case, print the maximum reward one can get after visiting the rooms in the order specified.
Print the output of each test case in a separate line.

You are not required to print the expected output; it has already been taken care of. Just implement the function.
